WEBVTT

00:06.089 --> 00:14.077
[SPEAKER_92]: Located between Silver Lake to the west and Chinatown to the east, Echo Park Lake has been a central part of the community since the 19th century.

00:14.617 --> 00:23.506
[SPEAKER_92]: The lake was originally created in 1868 as a drinking water reservoir, with water supplied by a ditch connecting it to the Los Angeles River near Los Feliz.

00:23.966 --> 00:28.290
[SPEAKER_92]: Soon after, 33 acres of land were donated to the city to establish a public park.

00:28.731 --> 00:35.117
[SPEAKER_92]: During landscaping in 1892, workers noticed sounds echoing across the area, inspiring the name Echo Park.

00:35.097 --> 00:39.365
[SPEAKER_92]: Today, the lake features a flat one-mile loop popular with walkers and runners.

00:39.806 --> 00:48.803
[SPEAKER_92]: Local running groups often train here, including members of the Los Angeles Fire Department, who are among the 27,000 runners participating in the Los Angeles Marathon.

00:50.892 --> 00:57.366
[SPEAKER_79]: We are at Dodger Stadium, and I believe it's about 6.30 a.m. in the morning, half hour before the start time of the L.A. Marathon.

00:57.386 --> 01:07.888
[SPEAKER_77]: For me, this is my tenth year in a row running the L.A. Marathon, and every year I run it for a charity that hits close to home with us, Widows, Orphans, and Disabled Firefighters Fund.

01:07.868 --> 01:13.003
[SPEAKER_31]: Personally, it's my first one, and I didn't fundraise, but Kelly here did.

01:13.425 --> 01:19.262
[SPEAKER_91]: By doing fundraising like this, it brings great attention to all the different foundations that you might not know about.

01:19.623 --> 01:21.810
[SPEAKER_91]: I think that's awesome, and there's a bunch of different ones.

01:48.233 --> 01:51.277
[SPEAKER_91]: We are supporting my twin sister.

01:51.317 --> 01:54.260
[SPEAKER_91]: She had foot surgery, like, two years ago.

01:54.280 --> 02:06.134
[SPEAKER_91]: So being in a marathon is, like, impossible to think of.

02:06.154 --> 02:10.940
[SPEAKER_25]: So it's great to see her out here and proving us all wrong.

02:10.960 --> 02:14.764
[SPEAKER_25]: You only live once, so you might as well, while you have the chance, go run it.

02:17.613 --> 02:18.494
[SPEAKER_56]: You gotta try it once.

02:18.895 --> 02:24.162
[SPEAKER_56]: Anything for a good cause, anything to promote health, nutrition, support the community as a whole.

02:32.194 --> 02:35.579
[SPEAKER_25]: My wife is running, this is her first official full marathon.

02:35.599 --> 02:37.061
[SPEAKER_25]: She's running this for her 40th birthday.

02:37.321 --> 02:42.068
[SPEAKER_25]: She's had some health struggles that she's overcome and so it's a huge achievement for her to accomplish this today.

02:49.321 --> 02:54.491
[SPEAKER_91]: not a sprint, so kind of like use that metaphor in your head, just keep going, don't stop.

02:54.811 --> 03:02.706
[SPEAKER_25]: You face so many obstacles and hurdles in your life that you have to overcome, you have to persevere through, and I feel like running a marathon is exactly that.

03:05.420 --> 03:10.467
[SPEAKER_79]: I helped this year with putting together a fire department marathon team for the Los Angeles Fire Department.

03:10.487 --> 03:15.594
[SPEAKER_79]: I think it's good to get the legs going and keep the fitness standards up to where they should be with our department.

03:15.755 --> 03:22.544
[SPEAKER_31]: Being a part of this running community within our smaller organization has really motivated me to train hard.

03:22.805 --> 03:28.052
[SPEAKER_77]: Being able to run through the city that you work in is actually a pretty awesome experience.

03:28.910 --> 03:31.153
[SPEAKER_11]: All running's gonna hurt regardless.

03:31.614 --> 03:38.804
[SPEAKER_11]: You definitely just have to go out and do it, and once you're finished with it, it's so gratifying at the end, and it's infinitely worth it.

03:39.345 --> 03:41.548
[SPEAKER_35]: We are at almost the 26-mile marker.

03:41.848 --> 03:47.416
[SPEAKER_35]: It's just a lot of cheering people on and getting people excited and giving them that last little push before they cross the finish line.

03:47.757 --> 03:50.260
[SPEAKER_35]: Right here is where they need the last push the most.

04:04.516 --> 04:09.264
[SPEAKER_77]: They gave me some extra swag for 10 years in a row, a little tenure medal.

04:16.557 --> 04:20.764
[SPEAKER_22]: To be a good firefighter for the City of Los Angeles, the number one thing is heart.

04:21.506 --> 04:28.077
[SPEAKER_22]: You've got to have dedication and you've got to have a will to want to help people, to be a public servant.

04:28.141 --> 04:32.531
