47:26.567 --> 47:35.537
[SPEAKER_51]: Today, it is my pleasure to welcome the Consul General of Bulgaria to our Council Chambers this morning.

47:35.597 --> 47:51.535
[SPEAKER_51]: I'm here with Boyoko Ristov and his wife, as well as a special delegation from the Bulgarian community, as we recognize March 2026 as Bulgarian Cultural Heritage Month.

47:51.515 --> 47:56.142
[SPEAKER_51]: Consul General Rostov has worked closely with the Bulgarian community.

47:57.455 --> 48:05.423
[SPEAKER_51]: across the West Coast to promote Bulgarian culture, education, and the strong friendship between the U.S. and the Republic of Bulgaria.

48:05.784 --> 48:09.428
[SPEAKER_51]: We're honored to have your presence here at City Hall with us today.

48:10.248 --> 48:24.103
[SPEAKER_51]: The City of L.A. proudly celebrates its rich multicultural heritage and recognizes the invaluable contributions of diverse communities that strengthen the social, cultural, and economic fabric of our city.

48:24.083 --> 48:27.789
[SPEAKER_51]: The month of March holds special significance for the Bulgarian people.

48:28.430 --> 48:36.121
[SPEAKER_51]: March 3rd marks Bulgaria's National Liberation Day, commemorating the restoration of Bulgarian statehood.

48:36.782 --> 48:41.950
[SPEAKER_51]: In honor of this occasion, City Hall was illuminated in the colors of the Bulgarian flag.

48:42.771 --> 48:52.065
[SPEAKER_51]: Bulgaria is one of Europe's oldest nations, with more than 13 centuries of history and a remarkable cultural legacy.

48:52.045 --> 49:01.875
[SPEAKER_51]: The Bulgarian people have given the world the Cyrillic alphabet, an enduring contribution to global literacy used by hundreds of millions of people today.

49:02.676 --> 49:16.551
[SPEAKER_51]: March also brings Bulgaria's most cherished traditions, Baba Marta, when friends and family exchange red and white Martin Tisza bracelets as a symbol of health, good fortune, and the arrival of spring.

49:16.531 --> 49:24.283
[SPEAKER_51]: For those who've never had an opportunity to visit Bulgaria, it is a place of extraordinary beauty and history.

49:25.404 --> 49:33.156
[SPEAKER_51]: There are ancient cities of Plotiv, one of the oldest continuously inhabited cities in Europe.

49:33.372 --> 49:38.339
[SPEAKER_51]: and the famous Rose Valley where the world's finest rose oil has been produced for centuries.

49:38.860 --> 49:46.372
[SPEAKER_51]: So it is my honor to get to present the Consul General with this resolution this morning on behalf of the city of Los Angeles.

49:46.452 --> 49:48.194
[SPEAKER_51]: Welcome again to our council chambers.

49:48.314 --> 49:49.596
[SPEAKER_51]: It's lovely to have you with us.

49:51.599 --> 49:57.388
