50:48.239 --> 50:57.494
[SPEAKER_74]: So today, members, Council President and members, we are honored to be honoring the Irish spirit in City Hall to celebrate St. Patrick's Day.

50:58.356 --> 51:06.930
[SPEAKER_74]: St. Patrick's Day is celebrated around the world on March 17th in honor of St. Patrick, the patron saint of Ireland, although we cannot forget St. Bridget, right?

51:07.653 --> 51:09.696
[SPEAKER_74]: But today, we're going to remember St. Patrick.

51:10.196 --> 51:18.507
[SPEAKER_74]: It marks the anniversary of his death in the 5th century and has become a global celebration of Irish culture and heritage around the world.

51:18.988 --> 51:32.125
[SPEAKER_74]: St. Patrick's Day is an opportunity to reflect and appreciate Irish culture, history, and the contributions to the world of the Irish people, including in literature, in music, in dance, and even in politics.

51:32.898 --> 51:38.042
[SPEAKER_74]: Whether you're Irish or just Irish at heart, St. Patrick's Day is a day of celebration, joy, and community.

51:38.685 --> 51:39.870
[SPEAKER_74]: Tomorrow.

51:40.019 --> 51:41.040
[SPEAKER_74]: for example, in the 1-5.

51:42.762 --> 52:00.244
[SPEAKER_74]: We are going to be hosting our annual Gaelic and Garlic Celebration so that we have the Italian-American culture and the Irish culture united in our brand new Piazza Miramare in downtown San Pedro, which is home to so many people of Italian heritage as well as Irish heritage.

52:00.925 --> 52:04.710
[SPEAKER_74]: But back to today, I want to introduce some guests.

