01:53:27.541 --> 01:53:38.357
[SPEAKER_90]: We're no longer iced out from government positions of power and decision making and want to make sure that we protect that and widen our ability to represent and govern ourselves.

01:53:38.558 --> 01:53:40.941
[SPEAKER_90]: And so just thank you so much for all that you've done.

01:53:40.961 --> 01:53:50.055
[SPEAKER_90]: I see you everywhere in our neighborhoods because you're a true CD14 resident or, you know,

01:53:50.035 --> 01:54:17.258
[SPEAKER_76]: Compañero, and this is the neighborhoods that you built and you're really there So appreciate everything that you do and thank you all of you for all the work that you've done Thank you so much councilmember ramen I just Sir you're disrupting the meeting this is your first warning and That's your second warning, and you're leaving and that's excellent because you're dismissed all right

01:54:18.149 --> 01:54:18.950
[SPEAKER_76]: Councilmember on it.

01:54:19.090 --> 01:54:20.753
[SPEAKER_63]: Thank you so much councilmember Hernandez.

01:54:20.773 --> 01:54:40.883
[SPEAKER_63]: Thank you for bringing this presentation forward senator Polanco and everyone who is here It's just been really incredible to listen to your memories of building power and to understand that where we are today came about because of the work that and the vision that you had for it and Every step that you took towards it

01:54:41.268 --> 01:55:00.639
[SPEAKER_63]: It's been awe-inspiring to hear it and to understand what it took to build it and to know that if we want to continue building that power today, we have to be as deliberate, as thoughtful, as generous to other people, as open to bringing more people into this work as you were.

