01:56:20.402 --> 01:56:20.602
[SPEAKER_76]: Thank you.

01:56:20.622 --> 01:56:22.285
[SPEAKER_76]: Thank you so much, Council Member Hutt.

01:56:22.325 --> 01:56:23.287
[SPEAKER_76]: Council Member Padilla.

01:56:25.511 --> 01:56:29.018
[SPEAKER_59]: Let me begin by saying that I want to be invited to the square opening as well.

01:56:29.200 --> 01:56:34.646
[SPEAKER_59]: So, you know, I'm looking at my talking points and I'm not going to say anything that wasn't already said.

01:56:35.908 --> 01:56:40.273
[SPEAKER_59]: Because I think what's more important is for me to just take this opportunity to say thank you.

01:56:41.474 --> 01:56:53.368
[SPEAKER_59]: When I hear your guys' history, I have a lot of gratitude for what it is that you did to at least have Latinos be taken serious to run for office.

01:56:53.348 --> 01:56:54.671
[SPEAKER_59]: in general, to start.

01:56:55.252 --> 01:57:03.651
[SPEAKER_59]: And I'm very grateful that because of that early work, now we're in a position where voters have multiple Latinos to choose from sometimes on the ballot.

01:57:04.132 --> 01:57:05.916
[SPEAKER_59]: But that took work.

01:57:06.216 --> 01:57:11.087
[SPEAKER_59]: And it's nice to see everyone together who helped get us to that place.

01:57:11.067 --> 01:57:16.436
[SPEAKER_59]: You know, in a few minutes, I'm supposed to do a video for Women's History Month.

01:57:16.456 --> 01:57:22.046
[SPEAKER_59]: And one of the questions that I have to answer is what inspired you to get involved in politics?

01:57:22.687 --> 01:57:25.392
[SPEAKER_59]: And I'm like, what a day to answer that question.

01:57:25.953 --> 01:57:32.805
[SPEAKER_59]: Because two of the people that exposed me first to local politics are right in front of me, you know.

01:57:33.781 --> 01:57:44.956
[SPEAKER_59]: Richard Alarcon, my nephew, is now enjoying, to today, that water slide that you put at Sun Valley Park, where I was invited in third grade to be part of the press conference.

01:57:46.298 --> 01:57:50.824
[SPEAKER_59]: And then Tony Cardenas, you were the first one that exposed me to working in campaigns.

01:57:51.665 --> 01:58:01.999
[SPEAKER_59]: You were the first one to expose me to what it's like to actually go into someone's living room and talk to them about the vision for the community.

01:58:01.979 --> 01:58:09.747
[SPEAKER_59]: There is still so many projects in my district that you started that because it takes so long to finish something, I'm still working on them.

