02:19:54.023 --> 02:19:56.646
[SPEAKER_18]: So we could talk about that later.

02:19:56.626 --> 02:20:08.137
[SPEAKER_18]: And I once had a grassroots leader say to me when I first started in Coachella Valley, his name was Gabriel, and he said, Zacharias, nadie es indispensable, pero todos somos necesarios.

02:20:08.738 --> 02:20:13.150
[SPEAKER_18]: Zachary, no one is indispensable, but we're all necessary.

02:20:13.130 --> 02:20:19.480
[SPEAKER_18]: Every single one of us is required to do the work of building our communities and our cities and creating the kind of world that we want to live in.

02:20:20.101 --> 02:20:26.510
[SPEAKER_18]: So it's a great relief to not be indispensable, and it's a great gift to be necessary.

02:20:26.731 --> 02:20:29.535
[SPEAKER_18]: I wish the same experience for each of you.

02:20:29.515 --> 02:20:30.116
[SPEAKER_18]: C.S.

02:20:30.176 --> 02:20:40.277
[SPEAKER_18]: Lewis, the great atheist-turned-Christian writer, once said that when we die, God doesn't ask us who we were doing something good for, like if we were doing it for God.

02:20:40.838 --> 02:20:45.027
[SPEAKER_18]: But instead, God looks at what we did and says, whatever you did that was good,

02:20:45.007 --> 02:20:46.811
