02:24:00.928 --> 02:24:04.772
[SPEAKER_76]: And you provide a way for them to get involved and help shape the world for all of us.

02:24:04.832 --> 02:24:07.195
[SPEAKER_76]: And so for that, we're extremely grateful.

02:24:07.776 --> 02:24:08.637
[SPEAKER_76]: Council Member Jurado.

02:24:09.238 --> 02:24:10.599
[SPEAKER_90]: Thank you, Council President.

02:24:10.960 --> 02:24:17.247
[SPEAKER_90]: And so on behalf of the city of Los Angeles, we present this plaque to honor your legacy at LA Voice.

02:24:23.099 --> 02:24:26.402
[SPEAKER_76]: While the pictures are flashing, we've got another speaker.

02:24:29.565 --> 02:24:30.646
[SPEAKER_76]: Council Member Yaroslavsky.

02:24:30.666 --> 02:24:46.261
[SPEAKER_64]: Yeah, just real fast, I want to add my voice to the chorus, thanking you, Reverend, for the work that you and LA Voice do at this moment right now, having interfaith work, moving Los Angeles forward in ways that benefit all Angelenos is something that we desperately need.

02:24:46.401 --> 02:24:51.486
[SPEAKER_64]: And the space that you create, the community that you build to push forward,

02:24:51.685 --> 02:24:54.874
[SPEAKER_64]: toward a brighter future for our city is something that I'm really grateful for.

02:24:54.894 --> 02:24:59.707
[SPEAKER_64]: I'm really grateful for the partnership that you and my team have been able to build and develop.

02:24:59.767 --> 02:25:02.133
[SPEAKER_64]: And so congratulations on this well-deserved honor.

02:25:02.234 --> 02:25:02.595
[SPEAKER_64]: Thank you.

02:25:03.798 --> 02:25:04.420
[SPEAKER_76]: Thank you so much.

02:25:04.460 --> 02:25:07.568
[SPEAKER_76]: Congratulations again, Reverend Zach Hoover and LA Voice.

02:25:18.685 --> 02:25:26.367
[SPEAKER_76]: All right, as they are departing to do photos, we want to recognize Council District 11.

02:25:49.094 --> 02:25:51.577
[SPEAKER_51]: All right.

02:25:51.897 --> 02:25:59.024
[SPEAKER_51]: This is so exciting.

02:26:00.025 --> 02:26:00.466
[SPEAKER_51]: All right.

02:26:00.526 --> 02:26:01.447
[SPEAKER_51]: Good morning, everyone.

02:26:01.527 --> 02:26:16.823
[SPEAKER_51]: And thank you, Council President, for the opportunity to recognize Coach Dylan Smith from Pali High as the 2025 AFC Don Shula High School Coach of the Year.

02:26:16.803 --> 02:26:23.496
[SPEAKER_51]: As you all know, LA has a long and proud football tradition.

02:26:23.556 --> 02:26:32.213
[SPEAKER_51]: Programs like Crenshaw, Dorsey, Birmingham, Venice, and Loyola, just to name a few.

02:26:32.699 --> 02:26:39.891
[SPEAKER_51]: have produced generations of great players in a city known for competing at the highest level.

02:26:40.752 --> 02:26:42.314
[SPEAKER_51]: And it's not just local pride.

02:26:42.895 --> 02:26:49.206
[SPEAKER_51]: California has produced more NFL players than any other state in the country.

02:26:49.847 --> 02:26:58.200
[SPEAKER_51]: That tells you something about the level of talent and competition at our high school programs every season.

02:26:58.180 --> 02:27:05.587
[SPEAKER_51]: So when a team like Pali Charter High puts together the kind of season they did in 2025, it means something.

02:27:06.588 --> 02:27:09.531
[SPEAKER_51]: Coach Smith was nominated by the LA Chargers.

02:27:10.111 --> 02:27:24.525
[SPEAKER_51]: He and Dave Ettinger of Garden City High School in New York were recognized at the Pro Bowl game and attended the last Super Bowl as guests of the NFL, where they got to walk the red carpets and get NFL honors.

02:27:24.809 --> 02:27:33.243
[SPEAKER_51]: The Don Shula High School Coach of the Year Award is named after pro football Hall of Famer Don Shula, the winningest coach in NFL history.

02:27:33.984 --> 02:27:44.421
[SPEAKER_51]: Each year, all 32 NFL clubs nominate a high school coach for the honor, with one winner selected from each conference.

02:27:44.823 --> 02:27:59.506
[SPEAKER_51]: Nominees are judged on the values that Coach Shula exemplified, character, integrity, leadership, commitment to the community, player health and safety, and on-field success.

02:28:00.707 --> 02:28:08.299
[SPEAKER_51]: Coach Smith earned this recognition after guiding the Dolphins through a season filled with undeniable adversity.

02:28:08.802 --> 02:28:18.057
[SPEAKER_51]: The Palisades fire destroyed the Pali High football field, the weight room, and equipment, leaving the program without a home base.

02:28:18.918 --> 02:28:22.884
[SPEAKER_51]: Ten players lost their homes in the blaze.

02:28:23.966 --> 02:28:31.738
[SPEAKER_51]: But rather than walk away from the season, Coach Smith and his staff found a way to keep the program going.

02:28:31.988 --> 02:28:36.272
[SPEAKER_51]: The team practiced and played at alternate sites all over the city.

02:28:36.873 --> 02:28:38.094
[SPEAKER_51]: They borrowed equipment.

02:28:38.654 --> 02:28:41.958
[SPEAKER_51]: They pulled together resources from anywhere they could.

02:28:42.859 --> 02:28:48.744
[SPEAKER_51]: Coach Smith even reached out to the LA Chargers, and the organization stepped up to support the team.

02:28:49.665 --> 02:29:00.816
[SPEAKER_51]: Under his leadership, Pally High completed a perfect 10-0 regular season and earned a berth in the city section Open Division playoffs.

02:29:00.836 --> 02:29:01.877
[SPEAKER_51]: That's awesome.

02:29:03.933 --> 02:29:06.800
[SPEAKER_51]: With that, we have a short video that we'd like to share.

02:29:06.860 --> 02:29:18.246
[SPEAKER_10]: Our Don Shula Coach of the Year Award nominee, to a coach who exemplifies integrity, achievement, and leadership, Palisades High School coach, Dylan Smith.

02:29:18.327 --> 02:29:20.009
[SPEAKER_68]: Last year I didn't know if I was gonna have a program.

02:29:20.470 --> 02:29:22.172
[SPEAKER_68]: We were debating on having a team.

02:29:22.212 --> 02:29:24.916
[SPEAKER_68]: We thought we lost the school, so we didn't know if kids were gonna transfer.

02:29:24.936 --> 02:29:26.238
[SPEAKER_68]: We didn't know if we were gonna have facilities.

02:29:26.479 --> 02:29:29.022
[SPEAKER_68]: Just next to me is Palisades High School.

02:29:29.082 --> 02:29:31.045
[SPEAKER_35]: This is the high school to my left.

02:29:31.165 --> 02:29:32.106
[SPEAKER_35]: The high school is burning.

02:29:32.267 --> 02:29:35.872
[SPEAKER_68]: My philosophy is just really to approach each day like it's your last.

02:29:35.992 --> 02:29:37.554
[SPEAKER_68]: You never know what tomorrow's gonna bring.

02:29:37.594 --> 02:29:42.301
[SPEAKER_68]: Obviously with the fires, one day we were ready for the off season, the next day it was almost taken from us.

02:29:42.341 --> 02:29:45.105
[SPEAKER_68]: So I just have the kids approach each day like it's their last.

02:29:45.225 --> 02:29:46.647
[SPEAKER_68]: We practice hard from,

02:29:46.627 --> 02:29:48.331
[SPEAKER_68]: the first whistle to the last whistle.

02:29:48.372 --> 02:29:50.537
[SPEAKER_68]: And like I said, tomorrow's not promised to you.

02:29:51.179 --> 02:29:51.881
[SPEAKER_68]: Neither is a game.

02:29:51.901 --> 02:29:56.613
[SPEAKER_68]: You can get hurt in the next play, but is your last play going to be your best play?

02:29:56.633 --> 02:29:58.257
[SPEAKER_04]: Again, just wanted to thank you guys coming out.

02:29:58.507 --> 02:30:00.730
[SPEAKER_04]: I know, obviously, it's been a tough couple of months.

02:30:01.030 --> 02:30:06.738
[SPEAKER_04]: We realize how powerful sports are, and in particular, football, and really what it means to a community.

02:30:07.239 --> 02:30:09.602
[SPEAKER_68]: The Chargers have been amazing since day one.

02:30:09.843 --> 02:30:15.691
[SPEAKER_68]: I remember emailing the Chargers and saying, if you guys have any old equipment that you guys are throwing away, we'll take it.

02:30:16.291 --> 02:30:19.956
[SPEAKER_68]: And Zach called me the next day, and we talked for about 30 minutes.

02:30:20.057 --> 02:30:23.241
[SPEAKER_68]: And he said he was going to be with us for this whole ride.

02:30:23.281 --> 02:30:26.185
[SPEAKER_68]: And he's done exactly what he said he was going to do.

02:30:26.165 --> 02:30:28.168
[SPEAKER_43]: The team overcame incredible odds.

02:30:28.188 --> 02:30:30.491
[SPEAKER_43]: 11 players lost homes in the fire.

02:30:30.992 --> 02:30:35.397
[SPEAKER_43]: Practices were held at no less than 10 different venues with no campus to call home.

02:30:36.118 --> 02:30:42.707
[SPEAKER_43]: And home games were played at two different sites, including Senior Night at SoFi Stadium.

02:30:42.727 --> 02:30:49.557
[SPEAKER_43]: He led the Dolphins to an undefeated regular season, turning the tragedy of the devastating Palisades fire into triumph.

02:30:50.898 --> 02:30:52.140
[SPEAKER_71]: All right, we got some news for you.

02:30:52.541 --> 02:30:52.781
[SPEAKER_71]: You ready?

02:30:52.801 --> 02:30:53.762
[SPEAKER_71]: Yes.

02:30:53.782 --> 02:30:55.885
[SPEAKER_71]: You were the chargers.

02:30:56.405 --> 02:30:59.457
[SPEAKER_71]: nominee for NFL coach of the year.

02:31:00.461 --> 02:31:05.622
[SPEAKER_71]: You won the Don Shula AFC NFL coach of the year.

02:31:09.010 --> 02:31:11.394
[SPEAKER_68]: Zach, the Spinos, the whole organization.

02:31:11.895 --> 02:31:17.665
[SPEAKER_68]: You guys have been with us since day one and for the rest of the NFL, this is what an organization means by community.

02:31:17.825 --> 02:31:20.149
[SPEAKER_68]: You guys have been on top of it since last year.

02:31:20.430 --> 02:31:24.497
[SPEAKER_56]: I wanted to say thank you Coach Smith for everything you've done for us, you know, the team.

02:31:24.617 --> 02:31:25.519
[SPEAKER_56]: It really means a lot.

02:31:25.539 --> 02:31:28.384
[SPEAKER_56]: You're such an inspiration to us and congrats on winning Coach of the Year.

02:31:28.704 --> 02:31:30.968
[SPEAKER_56]: By the way, you've won a brand new Toyota Tacoma.

02:31:30.948 --> 02:31:36.214
[SPEAKER_68]: When they gifted me with the truck and turned around and saw the whole team there, it was just an unbelievable feeling.

02:31:36.274 --> 02:31:43.081
[SPEAKER_68]: And it doesn't matter what I do, if the kids aren't there every day to put their body on the line, you know, nothing I do is going to matter.

02:31:45.283 --> 02:31:45.443
[SPEAKER_51]: Wow.

02:31:47.045 --> 02:31:54.373
[SPEAKER_51]: Coach, in a year when we needed wins, you delivered.

02:31:55.248 --> 02:31:59.313
[SPEAKER_51]: Coach Smith himself has deep roots in Southern California football.

02:32:00.154 --> 02:32:11.367
[SPEAKER_51]: He was a quarterback at Santa Monica High, then he played at Santa Monica College before becoming the starting quarterback at the University of Kansas in 1999 and 2000.

02:32:12.628 --> 02:32:25.103
[SPEAKER_51]: After his playing career, he transitioned into coaching, serving two stints as an assistant at Malibu High and then spending nine seasons as an assistant coach at the Brentwood School.

02:32:25.572 --> 02:32:33.321
[SPEAKER_51]: In February of 2023, he was hired as the 13th head football coach at Pali Hai.

02:32:33.689 --> 02:32:41.698
[SPEAKER_51]: The challenges his team faced last year mirrored the broader challenges faced by the entire Palisades High School community.

02:32:42.679 --> 02:32:53.031
[SPEAKER_51]: The fire, of course, damaged or destroyed most of the campus, forcing students to a temporary campus in Santa Monica in Visear's building.

02:32:53.912 --> 02:33:02.802
[SPEAKER_51]: Enrollment dropped, families were displaced, students faced long commutes and limited facilities.

02:33:03.136 --> 02:33:13.330
[SPEAKER_51]: And yet, through all of that, Pali High kept moving forward and the football team played right through the adversity.

02:33:14.933 --> 02:33:22.984
[SPEAKER_51]: One year and 20 days after the fire, we proudly welcomed the Pali Dolphins back to their home campus.

02:33:23.386 --> 02:33:30.875
[SPEAKER_51]: The resilience of these students, these families, and this school community is something that the entire city should be proud of.

02:33:31.656 --> 02:33:40.105
[SPEAKER_51]: So at this time, I'd like to bring forward Stuart and Aiden Wilson-Turner, a parent and student athlete, to say a few words.

02:33:40.526 --> 02:33:41.027
[SPEAKER_51]: Come on up.

02:33:47.014 --> 02:33:47.694
[SPEAKER_02]: Hello, everyone.

02:33:48.235 --> 02:33:51.739
[SPEAKER_02]: My name is Aiden Wilson-Turner, and I play safety for Palisades High.

02:33:51.989 --> 02:33:54.633
[SPEAKER_02]: where I'm currently in my junior year.

02:33:54.653 --> 02:33:57.658
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm glad today to talk about my coach, Coach Smith.

02:33:58.599 --> 02:34:06.852
[SPEAKER_02]: To most people, he's a football coach, but to me and the rest of the team, he's someone who truly shapes who we will become as we continue to grow.

02:34:07.894 --> 02:34:13.203
[SPEAKER_02]: He teaches us discipline, accountability, and what it means to show up for your teammates every single day.

02:34:14.424 --> 02:34:19.212
[SPEAKER_02]: Football's a tough sport, and Coach Smith pushes us to work harder than we think we can.

02:34:19.630 --> 02:34:29.667
[SPEAKER_02]: But more importantly, he reminds us that the lessons we learn on the field, teamwork, perseverance, and respect carry into our lives off the field as well.

02:34:29.687 --> 02:34:35.017
[SPEAKER_02]: Coach believes in his players and that belief pushes us to become better athletes, better students, and better people.

02:34:36.359 --> 02:34:43.592
