02:39:53.523 --> 02:39:55.185
[SPEAKER_60]: It was all good for our mental health.

02:39:55.646 --> 02:39:58.129
[SPEAKER_60]: So thank you so much, and congratulations.

02:39:58.149 --> 02:39:59.351
[SPEAKER_76]: Thank you so much, Council Member Hutt.

02:39:59.851 --> 02:40:01.133
[SPEAKER_76]: Council Member Rodriguez.

02:40:02.412 --> 02:40:02.812
[SPEAKER_65]: Thank you.

02:40:02.832 --> 02:40:14.865
[SPEAKER_65]: I just thank you, Council Member Park, for always bringing in these kind of shining lights and examples of what has really kind of happened out of the ashes, right?

02:40:15.065 --> 02:40:28.740
[SPEAKER_65]: It's your contributions, the stories of resilience that continue to be brought forward, and the recognition, the well-deserved recognition and celebration of your body of work.

02:40:28.720 --> 02:40:30.081
[SPEAKER_65]: I just want to say thank you.

02:40:30.121 --> 02:40:40.531
