[SPEAKER_59]: So I want to let you know that I appreciate you also pushing for the art component and the PE component.

03:06:07.460 --> 03:06:17.150
[SPEAKER_59]: How do we not have a strong physical education component in our schools in the generation when the Olympics are coming back to Los Angeles, right?

03:06:17.531 --> 03:06:26.100
[SPEAKER_59]: How do we not have a strong arts education component when we know that there's a mandate now on behalf of the state to make it happen?

03:06:27.700 --> 03:06:30.648
[SPEAKER_59]: We are working so hard to bring back Hollywood jobs.

03:06:31.852 --> 03:06:39.634
[SPEAKER_59]: You know, if you want the Hollywood bull to thrive, if you want Hollywood to thrive, you need to have strong arts education.

03:06:40.508 --> 03:06:42.030
[SPEAKER_59]: So thank you for the fight.

03:06:42.451 --> 03:06:45.054
[SPEAKER_59]: And please know that in this building, you have allies.

03:06:45.655 --> 03:06:46.857
[SPEAKER_59]: So keep pushing hard.

03:06:47.578 --> 03:06:55.689
[SPEAKER_59]: As I mentioned in another presentation, I'm about to do a video about, you know, Women's History Month and what inspired me to get into politics.

03:06:56.410 --> 03:06:58.253
[SPEAKER_59]: It wasn't just looking at my local leaders.

03:06:59.074 --> 03:07:03.600
[SPEAKER_59]: A lot of why I am here today has a lot to do with my teachers.

03:07:04.201 --> 03:07:10.009
[SPEAKER_59]: I can still name every single one of my teachers from kindergarten to senior year.

03:07:09.989 --> 03:07:17.639
[SPEAKER_59]: because they played such a crucial role in my development and my leadership and my love and passion for Los Angeles.

03:07:18.661 --> 03:07:25.450
[SPEAKER_59]: If you go back to all the times I ran for office, I'm the one that made a quote to say, I'm an LAUSD alum.

03:07:26.411 --> 03:07:29.515
[SPEAKER_59]: Post that, everyone now says, I'm an LAUSD alum.

03:07:30.316 --> 03:07:31.177
[SPEAKER_59]: And I know you guys know that.

03:07:31.858 --> 03:07:33.000
[SPEAKER_59]: And I'm going to keep saying that.

03:07:33.541 --> 03:07:36.064
[SPEAKER_59]: So thank you, and please know that we have your backs.

03:07:39.875 --> 03:07:40.817
[SPEAKER_76]: Councilmember Hutt.

03:07:43.203 --> 03:07:44.145
[SPEAKER_60]: I am compelled.

03:07:47.392 --> 03:07:49.677
[SPEAKER_60]: A couple of things that you might want to know.

03:07:49.757 --> 03:07:54.087
[SPEAKER_60]: First, I want to say thank you to Councilmember Sotomayor Martinez, Councilwoman

03:07:54.488 --> 03:07:58.292
[SPEAKER_60]: Hernandez, I am a LA USD alum.

03:07:58.712 --> 03:08:06.240
[SPEAKER_60]: My mom was a UTLA teacher in the 60s at Jordan High School, and she did adult school.

03:08:06.260 --> 03:08:08.182
[SPEAKER_60]: So this really means something to me.

03:08:08.583 --> 03:08:12.787
[SPEAKER_60]: I also just want to echo my colleagues.

03:08:12.907 --> 03:08:21.576
[SPEAKER_60]: I just want this to go by without saying the things that Councilmember Padilla said are true.

03:08:22.754 --> 03:08:29.682
[SPEAKER_60]: We don't understand why we have to fight so hard every couple of years for our children, our teachers, our workers.

03:08:30.363 --> 03:08:33.046
[SPEAKER_60]: And so we all stand in solidarity with you.

03:08:33.666 --> 03:08:38.792
[SPEAKER_60]: And so even though it's a recess day, I guess we'll be in the streets on the 18th.

03:08:39.713 --> 03:08:41.275
[SPEAKER_60]: Is that the date?

03:08:41.675 --> 03:08:42.636
[SPEAKER_60]: Okay, thank you, Herman.

03:08:42.877 --> 03:08:43.778
[SPEAKER_60]: Thank you, Mr.

03:08:43.798 --> 03:08:44.478
[SPEAKER_60]: Chair.

03:08:44.498 --> 03:08:45.339
[SPEAKER_60]: Thank you.

03:08:45.359 --> 03:08:46.461
[SPEAKER_76]: Thank you, Council Member Hutt.

03:08:46.621 --> 03:08:47.682
[SPEAKER_76]: Council Member Rahman.

03:08:49.940 --> 03:09:18.158
[SPEAKER_63]: Thank you so much councilmember Soto Martinez and Hernandez for bringing this presentation forward and I just wanted to stand up and echo the words of some of my colleagues also as a Lusd mom I know the work that utla and 99 members bring to the classrooms bring to the schools My children are they love their school, and they love their teachers, and they love the staff that work there and

03:09:18.644 --> 03:09:24.873
[SPEAKER_63]: And the environment that they have is a product of the care and love that your members bring every single day to those schools.

03:09:25.534 --> 03:09:26.696
[SPEAKER_63]: And I'm so grateful for that.

03:09:27.477 --> 03:09:28.859
[SPEAKER_63]: It's just incredible.

03:09:29.540 --> 03:09:32.444
[SPEAKER_63]: When they get sick, they don't want to miss school.

03:09:33.465 --> 03:09:35.689
[SPEAKER_63]: They are upset about not going to school.

03:09:36.129 --> 03:09:41.417
[SPEAKER_63]: And it's all because of who is there and the environment that they create for them.

03:09:41.657 --> 03:09:48.347
[SPEAKER_63]: And so we're just, as parents in Los Angeles, I know how grateful we all are for what you do.

03:09:48.428 --> 03:09:55.247
[SPEAKER_63]: And I know that parents will stand with you in your efforts to fight for justice at the workplace.

03:09:55.288 --> 03:09:56.090
[SPEAKER_63]: So thank you very much.

03:09:56.732 --> 03:09:57.454
[SPEAKER_76]: Thank you so much.

