04:21:37.406 --> 04:21:47.316
[SPEAKER_51]: How is putting them in a private apartment with maybe occasional visits, whatever that level of service, how is that going to solve the underlying problem?

04:21:49.498 --> 04:21:52.602
[SPEAKER_05]: I'm not sure if anyone from, anyone else wants to address it.

04:21:52.962 --> 04:21:54.844
[SPEAKER_05]: I'll just say that we,

04:21:56.815 --> 04:22:05.404
[SPEAKER_05]: We currently house with city funds, with city resources, city housing, individuals, high acuity individuals.

04:22:05.904 --> 04:22:07.446
[SPEAKER_05]: And we do that now.

04:22:07.846 --> 04:22:09.468
[SPEAKER_05]: And we do that with the Inside Safe program.

04:22:09.488 --> 04:22:11.250
[SPEAKER_05]: We do that with other interim housing programs.

04:22:11.790 --> 04:22:25.084
[SPEAKER_05]: And so we want a TLS program that can accommodate individuals that are currently in city-funded interim housing and can accommodate their transition to permanent housing

