04:24:03.327 --> 04:24:04.809
[SPEAKER_87]: That's how it's regionally priced right now.

04:24:04.989 --> 04:24:17.404
[SPEAKER_87]: And I think that it may be helpful to hear a little bit more about, in the current TLS program that's regionally funded, 55% of participants are people who are eligible for permanent supportive housing.

04:24:17.464 --> 04:24:22.931
[SPEAKER_87]: So the current iteration of the time-limited subsidy program is already serving people with pretty acute needs.

04:24:23.592 --> 04:24:30.921
[SPEAKER_87]: And there has been quite a bit of success this year in helping those households to stabilize in their own homes, to get ongoing services.

04:24:31.154 --> 04:24:34.571
[SPEAKER_87]: and to get the support that they need to transition to permanent supportive housing.

04:24:35.476 --> 04:24:37.024
[SPEAKER_87]: And we have learned some things.

04:24:37.245 --> 04:24:39.898
[SPEAKER_87]: And so the slot cost for TLS that

04:24:40.520 --> 04:24:44.325
[SPEAKER_87]: Council approved in January for the new city program is higher.

04:24:44.345 --> 04:24:46.208
[SPEAKER_87]: The services costs are higher.

04:24:46.328 --> 04:24:57.764
[SPEAKER_87]: So we think that under the new city program, it will be possible to have slightly lower case manager to client ratios to provide more intensive services for people with acute needs.

04:24:58.164 --> 04:25:02.991
[SPEAKER_87]: So we're trying to build on what has worked and do it a little bit better under the next model.

04:25:04.433 --> 04:25:05.214
[SPEAKER_51]: OK. That's good to know.

04:25:05.234 --> 04:25:10.341
[SPEAKER_51]: But so if you are going to place somebody that has high acuity addiction or mental health

04:25:10.439 --> 04:25:21.896
[SPEAKER_51]: needs into an apartment building with other residents, what are the guardrails to make sure that person is not causing a problem or derailing the progress of others?

04:25:22.237 --> 04:25:22.497
[SPEAKER_51]: Sure.

04:25:22.898 --> 04:25:26.503
[SPEAKER_51]: Do you want to talk about how it's going now?

04:25:26.523 --> 04:25:30.389
[SPEAKER_76]: We're hoping the answer is that you won't place someone like that in an apartment and walk away.

04:25:31.371 --> 04:25:37.560
[SPEAKER_51]: I'm astounded that this is even an option, that we're going to put someone at that high level of risk into an independent living.

04:25:38.502 --> 04:25:42.567
