[SPEAKER_62]: It's on the Register of Historic Places.

04:58:17.808 --> 04:58:25.938
[SPEAKER_62]: The mission of Center for the Arts Eagle Rock is to be a cultural hub for the Northeast Los Angeles community and beyond.

04:58:26.759 --> 04:58:42.499
[SPEAKER_62]: We provide a creative environment for artists and members of our community to make art together and feel creatively inspired and connect them to the transcendent power of the arts.

04:58:46.192 --> 04:58:49.339
[SPEAKER_62]: We have a very robust programming slate.

04:58:49.359 --> 04:58:59.323
[SPEAKER_62]: We have an after school arts program called Imagine Studio where we bring contemporary artists into elementary schools in northeast Los Angeles.

04:59:01.582 --> 04:59:14.237
[SPEAKER_62]: We also have for families, we have a weekly doodle hour where children and their parents come and they draw like Matisse, they draw like Picasso, they learn to do character art, they do illustrations.

04:59:14.698 --> 04:59:17.381
[SPEAKER_62]: So they learn a different technique every week.

04:59:17.661 --> 04:59:24.990
[SPEAKER_62]: And to see a father and his five-year-old daughter drawing side by side, it just fills me with delight.

04:59:26.185 --> 04:59:38.622
[SPEAKER_62]: On the other end of the spectrum we have Drawing Lab that is an online drawing workshop and the median age of the artist is 80.

04:59:39.263 --> 04:59:51.720
[SPEAKER_62]: Friendships have come out of that and that's a really wonderful thing to see how art connects people and it expands your life in ways that you never thought possible.

04:59:54.687 --> 05:00:03.064
[SPEAKER_62]: Being the director for the Center, the most rewarding experiences I find are watching people blossom.

05:00:03.084 --> 05:00:09.838
[SPEAKER_62]: I think of the Center as a garden, and we're planting all of these seeds for the future.

05:00:09.898 --> 05:00:12.523
[SPEAKER_62]: People grow when they come here.

05:00:12.583 --> 05:00:15.970
[SPEAKER_62]: That is the philosophy of this place.

05:00:19.510 --> 05:00:33.976
[SPEAKER_62]: I think it's important that the city of Los Angeles support the creative dreams of the people who live here because people need to know that their inspiration matters.

05:00:35.139 --> 05:00:41.991
[SPEAKER_62]: If you want to be a painter, you want to be a sculptor, you want to be a printmaker, you can.

