05:54:04.762 --> 05:54:10.270
[SPEAKER_09]: Life is busy, especially in a city like Los Angeles, but it can also be uncertain.

05:54:10.911 --> 05:54:16.880
[SPEAKER_09]: A large-scale disaster like an earthquake, wildfire, or even civil unrest can happen at any time.

05:54:17.541 --> 05:54:19.364
[SPEAKER_09]: As part of the city's Ready Your L.A.

05:54:19.404 --> 05:54:26.655
[SPEAKER_09]: Neighborhood program, this video covers the basic steps that you can take during and after an emergency to keep your loved ones safe.

05:54:27.597 --> 05:54:31.883
[SPEAKER_09]: We will review earthquake, wildfire, and active shooter scenarios.

05:54:32.707 --> 05:54:36.532
[SPEAKER_09]: Angelenos know the big one is coming, but don't know when.

05:54:37.433 --> 05:54:40.817
[SPEAKER_09]: It's very important to learn about earthquake safety now.

05:54:41.698 --> 05:54:50.229
[SPEAKER_09]: If you are indoors when an earthquake strikes, drop immediately to the floor, take cover as soon as you see or feel shaking, and hold on.

05:54:51.050 --> 05:54:57.077
[SPEAKER_09]: If there is no table nearby, sit on the floor against a wall, away from windows and tall furniture.

05:54:57.428 --> 05:55:01.975
[SPEAKER_09]: Protect your head and neck with your arms and stay indoors until the shaking stops.

05:55:02.716 --> 05:55:10.327
[SPEAKER_09]: If you are outside, move to a clear area and stay away from anything that could fall on you, like buildings, power lines, or trees.

05:55:11.168 --> 05:55:16.596
[SPEAKER_09]: If you are at the beach, immediately move to higher ground and follow tsunami evacuation signs.

05:55:17.357 --> 05:55:20.802
[SPEAKER_09]: If you are driving, pull over to a clear location and stop.

05:55:21.222 --> 05:55:24.567
[SPEAKER_09]: Avoid bridges, overpasses, and power lines.

05:55:24.732 --> 05:55:29.210
[SPEAKER_09]: If you are in a wheelchair, lock your wheels, bend over, and cover your head.

05:55:30.174 --> 05:55:34.472
[SPEAKER_09]: For more information, visit the Earthquake Country Alliances website.

05:55:34.823 --> 05:55:36.545
[SPEAKER_09]: Now onto wildfire tips.

05:55:37.305 --> 05:55:43.291
[SPEAKER_09]: If you do not receive warning in advance of a wildfire, only collect your grab-and-go kit if it's safe to do so.

05:55:43.972 --> 05:55:46.374
[SPEAKER_09]: Follow evacuation orders and help others.

05:55:47.095 --> 05:55:50.338
[SPEAKER_09]: If moving through a smoke-filled area, stay low to the ground.

05:55:51.158 --> 05:56:01.388
[SPEAKER_09]: If you do receive a prepare-to-evacuate warning, gather your loved ones and pets, ready your go bags, charge your cell phones, and plan your evacuation route.

05:56:01.857 --> 05:56:04.802
[SPEAKER_09]: Lastly, let's talk about an active shooter situation.

05:56:05.603 --> 05:56:08.968
[SPEAKER_09]: An active shooter is someone who is trying to kill and injure people.

05:56:09.710 --> 05:56:16.641
[SPEAKER_09]: If you find yourself in such a situation, it's important to keep in mind the run, hide, fight survival principles.

05:56:17.522 --> 05:56:20.146
[SPEAKER_09]: Your first option is to drop everything and run.

05:56:20.186 --> 05:56:24.834
[SPEAKER_09]: If possible, try to help others escape, but do not attempt to move the wounded.

05:56:25.555 --> 05:56:28.219
[SPEAKER_09]: Once you're safe, call 911.

05:56:28.418 --> 05:56:31.321
[SPEAKER_09]: If you cannot escape, find the nearest hiding place.

05:56:31.942 --> 05:56:37.147
[SPEAKER_09]: Lock the door or block the entry to your hiding place with tables, chairs, or whatever you can find.

05:56:38.048 --> 05:56:40.751
[SPEAKER_09]: Make sure to silence your cell phone.

05:56:40.771 --> 05:56:43.614
[SPEAKER_09]: If you are out of all other options, then fight.

05:56:44.255 --> 05:56:47.198
[SPEAKER_09]: Try to incapacitate the shooter in whatever way possible.

05:56:47.919 --> 05:56:50.102
[SPEAKER_09]: And remember, commit to your actions.

05:56:50.642 --> 05:56:52.384
[SPEAKER_09]: Your life depends on it.

05:56:52.820 --> 05:57:00.393
[SPEAKER_09]: Once law enforcement arrives, remain calm, follow their instructions, and keep your hands free and visible at all times.

05:57:01.615 --> 05:57:06.704
[SPEAKER_09]: Learn more about active shooter protocols at runhidefightla.org.

05:57:07.666 --> 05:57:08.828
[SPEAKER_09]: It's not over just yet.

05:57:08.868 --> 05:57:14.237
[SPEAKER_09]: The aftermath of an emergency is still a crucial time for you to remain alert and aware.

05:57:14.757 --> 05:57:21.847
[SPEAKER_09]: Stay clear of hazards like downed power lines, damaged buildings, and avoid using gas until your gas line has been inspected.

05:57:22.568 --> 05:57:28.696
[SPEAKER_09]: Cooperate fully with public safety officials and listen to local radio and TV stations for updated information.

05:57:29.417 --> 05:57:35.025
[SPEAKER_09]: Avoid driving during this time and only use your vehicle if there is an evacuation order.

05:57:35.045 --> 05:57:43.397
[SPEAKER_09]: Recovery time for different emergencies varies, but conditions commonly remain unstable two hours to two days after the emergency.

05:57:43.715 --> 05:57:47.959
[SPEAKER_09]: If you have evacuated your home, don't re-enter until officials say it's safe.

05:57:48.820 --> 05:57:55.607
[SPEAKER_09]: If you're sheltering in place, it's important to assess and secure the area, checking for gas and water leaks or broken wiring.

05:57:56.408 --> 05:58:02.854
[SPEAKER_09]: If there is utility damage, turn them off at the source and check with your utility company before switching them on again.

05:58:03.775 --> 05:58:07.779
